A New York man has been curbed from committing an outrageous transgression: running in Central Park at 4:30am.

The jogger, self-described entrepreneur, author and worldwide connector Peter Shankman, was duly given a ticket as he and a running partner entered mile two of his scheduled 10-mile run on Thursday, training for an upcoming triathlon.

The NYPD officer who witnessed Shankman's early-morning workout informed him that 'the people's park' does not open until 6am and issued him with a summons.

