'A "hey, buddy, the park doesn't open until six, you need to run on the sidewalk outside" from the police officer wouldn't have sufficed?' he wrote on Facebook.

'Apparently not, since he made it clear that his boss was in the car with him, so he had to write me up.'

Shankman says he understands that the law is in place to prevent people staying in the park too late or sleeping on the benches, but that he entered early to work out.

'The last 12 years have really been about getting the city healthy, you know. No smoking in bars, no trans fats, and here I was, I was running, I was exercising, trying to lose a few more pounds before this race,' he told Pix 11.

'Thank god I wasn't holding a Big Gulp.'

